1 (9) If a provider is subject to a local ordinance that
2 conflicts with this act, this act supersedes the local ordinance.
3 Sec. 14u. If an individual submits an application for the
4 affordability program to the department, or contracted third-party
5 organization for the department, and the individual is a customer
6 of a provider that has its own low-income water affordability
7 program, the department or third-party organization must forward
8 the application directly to that customer's provider's plan
9 administrator.
10 Enacting section 1. This amendatory act takes effect 180 days
11 after the date it is enacted into law.
12 Enacting section 2. This amendatory act does not take effect
13 unless all of the following bills of the 103rd Legislature are
14 enacted into law:
15 (a) Senate Bill No. 248.
16 (b) Senate Bill No. 249.
17 (c) Senate Bill No. 251.
18 (d) Senate Bill No. 252.
